<br>
If a lore item drops should someone who already has the item roll on it?  <br>
<br>
Both times I saw this situation get nasty followed along the same lines - item drops, group rolls, winner tells someone else to loot it because they &quot;deserve&quot; it.  Someone else in the group complains because that must obviously mean that the highest roller already has one and can't loot it, and therefore it is &quot;understood&quot; that they are not allowed to roll.<br>
<br>
The first time this happened, the the fight got nasty because the highest roller didn't give it to the next highest roller, he gave it to someone in the group who actually needed it.  It could be argued that the winner either misread the rolls (the person he gave it to was 3rd highest), or actually thought it should go to someone who could use it as opposed to someone who would sell it.  The arguement went on for a half hour while the room respawned around us.  The casters were all threatening to gate out, the meleers were demanding an escort back to the zone, the 2nd highest roller was putting on a tremendous display of profanity while petitioning, and the person who looted the drop was screaming at the curse-happy petitioner for being a greedy bastard who couldn't stand the fact he lost the roll.  Through it all the high roller continued to swear he didn't already have one and thought the whole arguement was stupid.  The group ended up disbanding, and I doubt the petition ever got an answer, because no gm in their right mind would touch that arguement with a 10' pole.<br>
<br>
Round 2.  Item drops, everyone rolls, high roller passes it to the 2nd highest.  3rd highest inspects the winner, sees the item that just dropped, calls a reroll, and 4th highest backs him up.  (I still don't know why I end up dead last every time I roll on anything worth more than 100pp, but that's a different issue altogether <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> )  1st and 2nd argue, camp continues to spawn, group gets wiped out - fights through the entire CR, and the 2nd highest roller still walked away with the drop.  <br>
<br>
So then, is it supposed to be &quot;understood&quot; that someone can't roll on a duplicate lore?  Personally I see no reason why it should be a problem - it's no different than someone who can loot the item passing it on to someone else.  Is there some unspoken law spreading through the lands?  If the loot rules stated at the start of the group say ffa/roll on rare, and don't specify that people can't roll on duplicates, the gm is never going to order a reroll (despite the guy in the first example who insisted it was against Verant pnp to roll on an item you can't loot).<br>
<br>
If not for the fact that both events cost me endless wasted hours and some xp the second time around, I find the whole thing ridiculous.  What's the consensus on this one? <p><img src=http://www.kaseyspace.com/EQ/nenasig5.jpg align=center>
