I guess you must keep it hotkeyed to save time... <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/ukinid.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kinid</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>New to the block</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(7/21/01 4:18:58 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Rolling on Duplicate Lore</span><hr size=1> Pick up groups : Almost every group I'm in everyone rolls, even on class specific armor drops.  I'm a ranger and a tolans Bracer drops everyone in the group has the right to roll even if they aren't a ranger because of the trade value of the item for something they can use.  In the case of Lore items it's almost an unwritten rule not to roll on a lore item you already have.  Although playing Devil's advocate I really must question this rule.  example.. I have a RBG I'm in a pick up group in seb and an RBG drops should I roll ? well most would say no(and personally I wouldn't) but why?  just the fact that I am wearing my RBG and didn't dump it on a mule prior to coming to seb in the off chance of getting another helps the group by me actually using this item to the groups benefit.  now if I was dishonest and dumped it on a mule and used an fbss I would get to roll on the item I contributed to getting as much as any other group member.  Now you can surely bet that any cleric or other class that wouldn't wear an RBG which wins one.  First thing would dump that item on an alt so as not to be excluded from future drops.  So why should the mellee who wear the item be excluded. the value of such an item is the same to everyone involved due to the fact that at least 40% of peoples items are typically traded for.  By the same token you cant exclude a caster from melee loot especially in seb just for the fact that there is almost no caster loot in that dung.  This may be an extreme view, and is never and will never be practiced (nor do I care)but imho it is the only truly fair way to do things in a pickup group.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/udyschord.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Dyschord</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Been around a while</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(7/22/01 9:06:16 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Rolling on Duplicate Lore</span><hr size=1> I found a simple solution that seems to work for me...<br>
