"Who is this irresistable creature with an insatiable love of the dead?"</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/ulivtinth.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Livtinth</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Maztah Pozter</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(7/28/01 3:59:43 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Rolling on Duplicate Lore</span><hr size=1> if i'm in a real pickup group, and we lotto everything ffa, it's ffa, period. if someone wins something, he's sometimes out, sometimes still in (depends on the group). as for rolling on an item he already has: well that's simple, you can pick it up, you can roll for it. if you want to roll for it and you can't pick it up then you are very dumb. because in a real pickup group you could try to let another groupmember loot and give it to you later, but in most cases (and even when it's a minor item), the group will say &quot;you already have one and can't pick it up, why should one of us others loot and give it to you later?&quot;. so, it's your thing if you'll try to make it like that, or stay out of the lotto. if it comes to things like RBG/SBC for example, i can understand that the warrior who already has one would like to lotto for it too. he distributed as much to the kill and the loot (his time, that is) as everyone else in the group. but i'm not sure if i would trust a_pickup_groupmember_01 to loot my belt/cloak to give it to me later/another character in case that i win.<br>
